    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-07T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-07T12:00:00-05:00" n="199"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d199">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 <gloss target="#t_EW1">EW</gloss>/7–745:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 199 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Representative on the Allied Commission on
                        Reparations</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PEW1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Pauley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d199fn1">Sent over the signature of <persName
                            corresp="#p_HWA2">Harriman</persName>. Sent to Washington; relayed to
                            <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName>, then at sea, in telegram
                        No. 9 of July 9 (file No. 740.00119 (Potsdam)/8–645).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]<note n="2" xml:id="d199fn2">For the full text
                            of this message, see <ref target="#d370">document No. 370</ref>.</note>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-07T20:00:00+03:00"
                            >July 7, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2466. Top secret to the Secretary from <persName corresp="#p_PEW1"
                        >Pauley</persName>.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                <p>I consider it most important that the agenda of the coming conference provide for
                    consideration of these reparation matters<note n="3" xml:id="d199fn3">For the
                        details of the matters referred to, see <ref target="#d370">document No.
                            370</ref>.</note> as well as the question of the inclusion of
                        France.<note n="4" xml:id="d199fn4">i. e., in the Allied Commission on
                        Reparations.</note> You would favor me greatly if you would see that these
                    matters are given a high place on the agenda as they are questions of high
                    policy which must be determined.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
